710452f-a.text:
Tenth Ave., at Little West 12th Street, as seen from under the Wost Side Express Highway. Also shown, Little West 12th Street, south side, east from Tenth Ave., to and including Washington Street. Note Gansevoort
Market Stand on the right.
March 16, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
710452f-a.folder: 10th Avenue & Little West 12th Street, Manhattan, NY

710451f-a.text:
(1)
16-18 Tenth Ave., at the S.E. corner of Little West 12th Street. Note Gansevoort Market Stand, at the rear of the afore mentiened buildings.
April 2, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same; from a different angle, and viewing northward on Tenth Ave. Across market stand is seen a portion of the north side of Little
West 12th Street.
May 12, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)  The same, showing the frame structure at the rear of buildings. Also shown are Piers No. 53 to 56 Hudson River,(on the west side of
Eleventh Ave).
October 11, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

719979f-a.text:
(1)
Gansevoort Market Stand, northwestern quarten, view towards Tenth Avenue and Little West 12th Street. The sign "Sam Tennenbaum
Restaurant" is on the rear of 16-18 Tenth Avenue.
October 1, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, from a different angle and viewed in a more easterly direction, showing (extreme right) a portion of the New York Central Railroad trestle
on Washington Street.
March 3, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
